38:37.656 --> 38:39.998
- Superficial...
- And she's bleeding.

38:40.156 --> 38:41.406
- Winnie!
- Yes, Ma'am?

38:41.489 --> 38:43.647
- Come here! Come quick!
- Coming, Ma'am.

38:44.406 --> 38:46.446
- Come, hold this leg.
- Try to hold your arm still.

38:46.489 --> 38:47.535
All the way up.

38:47.614 --> 38:51.286
No damage to the carotid.
The sutures are overlapping.

38:52.572 --> 38:55.573
This baby's head's
wedged right in there.

39:00.698 --> 39:03.199
- I'm pulling out clots.
- It's an abrupted placenta.

39:04.073 --> 39:05.618
Okay, hold her flat.

39:09.656 --> 39:12.328
Wait.
What are we doing?

39:13.073 --> 39:14.368
I'm going to section her.

39:14.864 --> 39:16.240
You're going
to section her here?

39:16.323 --> 39:18.119
Yeah.
Give her the Ketamine.

39:19.031 --> 39:21.781
Listen to me.
Listen, listen.

39:22.281 --> 39:23.781
Listen, we'll do
everything we can

39:23.864 --> 39:25.206
for you and your baby, okay?

39:25.281 --> 39:26.281
Okay?

39:26.406 --> 39:27.952
Assatu, you're going
to be comfortable,

39:28.031 --> 39:29.077
you're going to be strong,

39:29.156 --> 39:30.476
and everything's
going to be okay.

39:31.115 --> 39:32.581
Okay, Ketamine's going in.

39:38.406 --> 39:41.407
- Refugees. Okay.
- Okay, everyone. I'm cutting.

39:54.447 --> 39:56.618
Okay, here we go.

39:58.823 --> 39:59.664
Okay, pull.

39:59.739 --> 40:01.018
I'm closing the neck wound.

40:14.115 --> 40:16.161
- Wow, it's really wedged.
- Yeah.

40:16.489 --> 40:17.535
Really wedged.

40:17.614 --> 40:20.115
Try to manipulate
the baby's head upward, please.

40:20.406 --> 40:21.531
Okay.

40:21.614 --> 40:24.206
Winnie. Legs up again.
All the way up.

40:24.280 --> 40:25.280
Yes, Ma'am.

40:25.364 --> 40:26.410
Up!

40:29.531 --> 40:30.531
More. Push.

40:30.698 --> 40:32.323
Wait.

40:35.572 --> 40:38.413
Okay. Head is out!

40:38.489 --> 40:40.206
- Syringe!
- Head is out.

40:44.447 --> 40:46.914
Okay. Fast.

40:48.447 --> 40:49.447
Okay.

40:51.656 --> 40:53.782
I have to rotate the baby.

40:55.531 --> 40:58.998
Okay. Okay, little one.

41:03.239 --> 41:04.535
Baby's out.

41:04.906 --> 41:06.281
Switch all to green.

41:06.364 --> 41:07.535
Okay, thank you.

41:07.614 --> 41:10.081
Okay. Okay. Cutting.

41:10.156 --> 41:12.531
- How is that'?
- Pulse rate is slow.

41:15.739 --> 41:17.535
<i>Let me. Let me.</i>

42:00.656 --> 42:04.123
Assatu's baby is doing well.
Assatu can rest.

42:37.280 --> 42:39.952
We both could do with
that bottle of whiskey, huh'?

42:40.989 --> 42:42.910
The sacrifices we make, huh?

43:16.280 --> 43:18.121
Are you kidding me?

43:23.614 --> 43:25.330
Is nothing sacred to you?

43:26.322 --> 43:28.197
Everything is sacred to me.

43:29.906 --> 43:31.156
Everything-

43:38.406 --> 43:41.247
There's a path that zigzags
the creek over there.

43:41.322 --> 43:43.573
I think that's the quickest
route to Sierra Leone.

43:43.656 --> 43:46.032
- Through the jungle?
- Through the jungle.

43:46.489 --> 43:47.785
You've got to be kidding.

43:47.989 --> 43:50.660
Don't think that the paths
aren't known by the bad guys.

43:50.739 --> 43:52.956
When you run
into them out there...

44:19.364 --> 44:21.160
There you go.

44:21.698 --> 44:23.073
Yeah.

44:24.197 --> 44:27.824
Thank you, in the name of Jesus.

44:28.155 --> 44:29.872
In the name of Jesus?

44:30.030 --> 44:32.747
I prefer it
in the name of you and me.

44:45.906 --> 44:50.202
Hey, listen, last night, I...
I overreacted.

44:50.489 --> 44:51.580
It's all right.

44:51.656 --> 44:53.372
You were embarrassed to kiss me

44:53.447 --> 44:55.823
with unbrushed teeth,
that's all.

45:01.197 --> 45:05.369
My father came and went a lot.
What does that tell you'?

45:06.030 --> 45:09.406
That we had different
experiences, that's all.

45:10.280 --> 45:12.996
- And?
- And nothing.

45:13.072 --> 45:15.448
It's nice to share
different experiences.

45:22.364 --> 45:24.035
<i>What about your mother?</i>

45:24.489 --> 45:26.615
<i>She had an affair.</i>

45:26.864 --> 45:29.205
<i>And then another affair.</i>

45:29.906 --> 45:32.827
<i>Maybe my dad was away too much.</i>

45:34.364 --> 45:39.365
<i>After my father died,
my mother wrote me.</i>

45:42.197 --> 45:43.993
<i>She told me she missed him.</i>

45:48.030 --> 45:51.531
<i>I don't even think
she called him for years.</i>

45:53.947 --> 45:56.073
<i>She mm me...</i>

45:57.280 --> 46:02.623
if I wanted a repetitive life.
I should see many men.

46:04.489 --> 46:08.410
But if I wanted
endless diversity, “

46:11.364 --> 46:13.911
I should slay with one.

46:15.406 --> 46:17.452
What do you think?

46:17.614 --> 46:20.330
Was your father away too much?

46:21.614 --> 46:24.364
I think children spell love...

46:25.698 --> 46:30.574
T-I...

46:31.280 --> 46:35.827
M-E.

46:44.947 --> 46:47.789
But I'm not a child anymore.

48:11.072 --> 48:14.289
<i>Miguel's attentions
diminished my fears</i>

48:14.364 --> 48:16.410
<i>in this terrifying place'</i>

48:17.239 --> 48:20.240
<i>This place.
At this time.</i>

48:21.614 --> 48:23.330
<i>Where children, fed mixtures</i>

48:23.406 --> 48:26.657
<i>of amphetamines
and hallucinogens,</i>

48:26.988 --> 48:29.080
<i>had been convinced by commanders</i>

48:29.155 --> 48:31.281
<i>that by the eating
of enemy hearts</i>

48:31.988 --> 48:34.955
<i>would they be
made invisible in battle.</i>

48:56.239 --> 48:57.740
I got it.

49:01.322 --> 49:03.664
- Okay?
- Don't stand there.

50:51.155 --> 50:52.315
I'm going to see if I can use

50:52.364 --> 50:53.955
a satphone to get
through to Paris.

50:54.030 --> 50:54.871
Okay.

50:54.947 --> 50:58.574
Hey. Another one
of Dr. Leon's babies.

50:58.738 --> 51:00.330
This one is both of ours.

51:05.489 --> 51:07.909
- Dr. Leon!
- I've got a patient.

51:08.155 --> 51:10.780
- Where should I take her?
- Medical NGOs are this way.

51:10.863 --> 51:12.205
They'll set up a tent for you.

51:13.280 --> 51:17.156
Hi. I'm project manager
at MDM.

51:17.239 --> 51:18.330
How can we help you today?

51:18.406 --> 51:19.465
We have a few refugees with us.

51:19.489 --> 51:20.809
I was hoping
to use your satphone.

52:24.531 --> 52:28.452
IRC requested us
to implement operations here.

52:29.697 --> 52:31.789
Oh, really?
What did you tell them?

52:32.863 --> 52:36.410
HQ approved,
so I volunteered us.

52:41.072 --> 52:42.572
"Us"?

52:44.697 --> 52:45.788
Mm-hmm.

52:47.447 --> 52:51.993
All of us, the four MDM staff
that came with us.

52:53.780 --> 52:55.530
Okay.

52:56.863 --> 52:58.534
That's nice.

52:59.697 --> 53:01.993
So, I've been demoted
to general practice.

53:07.406 --> 53:11.872
- Are you okay with that'?
- Yes, I'm okay with that,

53:14.863 --> 53:16.829
So, we're staying here.

53:18.239 --> 53:19.490
Okay.

53:22.114 --> 53:24.955
You should try
and get some sleep.

53:29.280 --> 53:31.372
I'm not tired.

53:33.072 --> 53:35.868
So. we're both not tired.

53:44.197 --> 53:45.322
Mm-hmm.

54:03.447 --> 54:05.788
Are you a playboy, Miguel?

54:10.280 --> 54:13.076
I'm not playing
anything here, Wren.

55:30.613 --> 55:32.705
Hmm. Hmm!

55:51.280 --> 55:52.495
Ahh!

56:32.822 --> 56:35.823
<i>We established
a clinic in the camp.</i>

56:35.947 --> 56:39.789
<i>Initial supplies had arrived
quickly by UN transport,</i>

56:39.863 --> 56:42.659
<i>and we made requests
of our own logisticians</i>

56:42.738 --> 56:45.659
<i>to set up sustainable
supply-chains.</i>

56:46.697 --> 56:49.198
<i>There is something
in propinquity,</i>

56:49.280 --> 56:52.655
<i>perhaps not to be confused
with fate.</i>

56:52.947 --> 56:55.198
<i>Only four days
before our arrival</i>

56:55.279 --> 56:56.325
<i>in Sierra Leone,</i>

56:56.405 --> 56:59.122
<i>I'd been</i> a <i>non-practicing
medical professional</i>

56:59.197 --> 57:00.868
<i>who'd taken on
the administration</i>

57:00.947 --> 57:04.698
<i>of my father's organization
from an office in Paris.</i>

57:04.780 --> 57:09.451
<i>New, I find myself reliving
for the first time...</i>

57:09.697 --> 57:12.244
<i>his extraordinary fife.</i>

57:13.571 --> 57:15.446
<i>I knew of my mother's affairs.</i>

57:15.530 --> 57:17.076
<i>But what of my father's'?</i>

57:17.155 --> 57:19.655
<i>Had he had a lover
as I had become Miguel's?</i>

57:20.655 --> 57:22.496
<i>The resilience and beauty</i>

57:22.571 --> 57:24.913
<i>offered by the refugees of war</i>

57:25.279 --> 57:28.621
<i>inspired an intoxication
of intimacy.</i>

57:28.947 --> 57:31.618
<i>And in this place
of so much war...</i>

57:32.863 --> 57:35.363
<i>Had I found peace?</i>

57:37.363 --> 57:39.580
<i>Or was I trading on Miguel's?</i>

57:41.780 --> 57:45.952
I want to see you
without me in the room.

57:57.530 --> 57:59.246
I know you are watching.

58:44.947 --> 58:47.118
I can feel you breathing.

59:00.154 --> 59:01.154
<i>You there'?</i>

59:37.613 --> 59:39.739
You're killing yourself.

59:49.446 --> 59:52.242
I just wanted
to say good-bye...

59:52.530 --> 59:57.998
and, uh, give you this back.

01:00:03.571 --> 01:00:06.913
You don't want to know
what I wrote in the letter?

01:00:10.947 --> 01:00:12.492
No,

01:00:17.154 --> 01:00:18.826
All right.

01:00:25.154 --> 01:00:26.245
<i>Do...</i>

01:00:28.030 --> 01:00:30.405
what's in the letter.

01:00:30.988 --> 01:00:32.613
Whatever it is.

01:00:36.530 --> 01:00:38.405
I can't.

01:00:38.738 --> 01:00:40.989
I can't, it's not...

01:00:41.113 --> 01:00:43.580
something I can "do."

01:00:45.321 --> 01:00:46.321
Never mind.

01:00:46.488 --> 01:00:48.534
- What were you gonna say?
- It can't just be said.

01:00:48.613 --> 01:00:50.613
Like what's in the letter
can't be "done"?

01:00:50.780 --> 01:00:53.451
Wren, I don't know
if it's all right

01:00:53.530 --> 01:00:54.872
to have said
what's in the letter,

01:00:55.488 --> 01:00:58.113
so I don't know
if I have the license to do it.

01:01:10.738 --> 01:01:15.455
I realized a while back
what it really was, the truth.

01:01:17.071 --> 01:01:19.117
What was the truth?

01:01:32.446 --> 01:01:35.117
You never loved me.

01:01:40.071 --> 01:01:42.037
I did love you, Wren.

01:01:42.279 --> 01:01:44.905
- No,
- MIGUEL: I do love you!

01:01:44.988 --> 01:01:49.079
Ten years."
You show up after ten years.

01:01:49.279 --> 01:01:51.120
Expecting what?

01:01:55.113 --> 01:01:57.159
- I do love you, Wren.
- You don't love me!

01:01:57.238 --> 01:01:59.284
You don't even know me!

01:01:59.488 --> 01:02:02.739
I'm different now,
that's what happens!

01:02:18.655 --> 01:02:21.371
Don't you fucking take
another step towards me!

01:02:21.446 --> 01:02:22.963
What? What? Or you'll what?
You'll shut down?

01:02:22.987 --> 01:02:25.238
Are you sure it's me
that made you shut down?

01:02:25.321 --> 01:02:26.867
<i>Wow.</i>

01:02:27.238 --> 01:02:30.489
Bravo! Bravo!
Is that what you learned to do'?

01:02:30.571 --> 01:02:32.211
Is that what you've taught
yourself to do?

01:02:32.738 --> 01:02:34.704
Make yourself
strong enough to black out

01:02:34.780 --> 01:02:36.030
what really fucked us up?

01:02:36.113 --> 01:02:37.659
Stop for a second!

01:02:40.697 --> 01:02:44.573
Wren, Wren, removing yourself,
blocking out does not change it.

01:02:44.655 --> 01:02:46.530
That's not gonna
make you happier.

01:02:47.946 --> 01:02:49.822
Take it from me, I know it.

01:02:51.196 --> 01:02:55.072
Wow. That's very good.
Way better than me.

01:02:55.363 --> 01:02:56.739
Wren.

01:02:56.822 --> 01:02:59.538
Wren!
Don't shit on what it was.

01:02:59.613 --> 01:03:01.839
We can't be explained away
with those short little sentences

01:03:01.863 --> 01:03:03.283
like "You never loved me."
Don't.

01:03:03.363 --> 01:03:05.534
Don't die in yourself
like those sheep

01:03:05.822 --> 01:03:08.447
in their comfortable
fund-raising fucking lives!

01:03:09.071 --> 01:03:10.868
That's not you, Wren.

01:03:10.946 --> 01:03:12.946
And I do know you,
that's not you.

01:03:13.488 --> 01:03:16.113
And if it was me
that changed you...

01:03:16.321 --> 01:03:18.992
Fuck me.
Don't let that happen.

01:03:19.488 --> 01:03:21.830
That would be a great loss.

01:03:23.029 --> 01:03:24.701
Fuck.

01:03:50.321 --> 01:03:51.321
Excuse me, Miss.

01:03:51.904 --> 01:03:55.451
Our school is raising money,
an organization that...

01:04:00.488 --> 01:04:04.079
Bless you. Bless you
in the name of Jesus.

01:04:04.279 --> 01:04:07.325
What about in the name
of you and me'?

01:04:09.571 --> 01:04:11.037
Mm.

01:04:13.029 --> 01:04:15.075
Thank you, Miss.

01:04:16.488 --> 01:04:18.363
<i>First-class
boarding announcement,</i>

01:04:18.446 --> 01:04:21.196
<i>Geneva to Cape Town.</i>

01:04:49.488 --> 01:04:51.286
<i>We hope
you have a pleasant flight.</i>

01:04:51.780 --> 01:04:55.076
<i>Flight time wilt be
11 and 15 minutes to Cape Town,</i>

01:04:55.321 --> 01:04:58.788
<i>arriving 2:47 p.m.
local time.</i>

01:05:30.196 --> 01:05:31.412
<i>I learned that Miguel</i>

01:05:31.488 --> 01:05:34.079
<i>had been raised
as a child of the state,</i>

01:05:34.154 --> 01:05:37.530
<i>orphaned in Spain's
transition to democracy,</i>

01:05:38.904 --> 01:05:40.405
<i>and that out of that
he put himself</i>

01:05:40.488 --> 01:05:43.580
<i>through medical school
with the highest honors.</i>

01:05:45.530 --> 01:05:48.576
<i>It occurred to me
that growing up in such a way,</i>

01:05:48.862 --> 01:05:51.283
<i>he was not subject
to the contradictions</i>

01:05:51.363 --> 01:05:52.783
<i>and hypocrisies</i>

01:05:53.154 --> 01:05:56.621
<i>that we, who'd been
raised in comfort,</i>

01:05:57.363 --> 01:05:58.829
too often accept.

01:05:59.154 --> 01:06:00.279
Hello, Oom Pieter!

01:06:00.946 --> 01:06:02.197
Hello, Miss Peterson!

01:06:02.279 --> 01:06:03.279
Good to see you!

01:06:03.446 --> 01:06:05.492
<i>Ja, dankie.</i>

01:06:05.571 --> 01:06:06.731
Is the key in the same place?

01:06:06.821 --> 01:06:08.413
Ja, welcome!

01:06:08.488 --> 01:06:09.488
Thank you!

